                        "displayName": "Antoine Pitrou",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Europe/Paris"
                    },
                    "body": "Uh... Calling the {{MemoryPool}} constructor creates an invalid MemoryPool object. It's surprising that {{pa.array}} accepts it silently and doesn't crash.\r\n\r\nI suppose {{MemoryPool.bytes_allocated()}} should check for the pointer being null and raise ValueError in that case. This is already done in other places (see e.g. {{Tensor._validate()}}).",
